UNITED STATES of America v. Martha CHOATE, also Known as Mrs. I. R. Choate, and A. J. Spadden. No. 3290. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Jan. 31, 1946. K. Gill Shaffer, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Albuquerque, N. M., for appellant. Otto Smith, of Clovis, N. M., for appel-lee.

Before PHILLIPS, Circuit Judge, and SYMES, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal docketed and dismissed on motion of appellant and pursuant to stipulation.
